	doi = {10.1016/j.buildenv.2017.12.010},
	abstract = {In this study, we propose a new control algorithm based on occupancy status for indoor environmental devices to maintain thermal comfort while saving energy of residential buildings. The algorithm consists of two parts: an environmental data driven model for the occupancy status detection and an integrated comfort algorithm for operating the indoor devices. To detect the occupancy status, a multinomial logistic regression model is developed based on the data obtained from passive infrared (PIR) sensors, a door sensor, CO2 concentrations, and lighting electricity consumption. The occupancy status is categorized into three classes: away, active, and inactive (sleep).},
